OL,3,CArtemis II astronauts rocket towards
OL,4,Cthe moon after leaving Earth's orbit
OL,6,FArtemis II astronauts are rocketing
OL,7,Ftowards the moon after leaving Earth's
OL,8,Forbit.
OL,10,FThe so-called translunar ignition came
OL,11,F25 hours after liftoff, putting the
OL,12,Fthree Americans and one Canadian on
OL,13,Fcourse for a lunar fly-around early
OL,14,Fnext week.
OL,16,F"Ladies and gentlemen, I am so, so
OL,17,Fexcited to be able to tell you that
OL,18,Ffor the first time since 1972 during
OL,19,FApollo 17, human beings have left
OL,20,FEarth orbit," NASA's Lori Glaze
OL,21,Fannounced at a news conference.
