OL,3,CArtemis II astronauts rocket towards
OL,4,Cthe moon after leaving Earth's orbit
OL,6,FNasa has said Artemis II will help
OL,7,F"explore the moon for scientific
OL,8,Fdiscovery, economic benefits, and to
OL,9,Fbuild the foundation for the first
OL,10,Fcrewed missions to Mars".
OL,12,FIf successful, it will pave the way
OL,13,Ffor Artemis III, currently planned for
OL,14,F2027, which aims to land astronauts on
OL,15,Fthe moon using a lunar-lander version
OL,16,Fof SpaceX's Starship rocket.
